Constructor Detail

Generator

public Generator(Field[] Col,
                 java.lang.String output,
                 int Records,
                 MainGui Parent)
This is the constructor method for the generator. It takes in a preconfigured array of Fields and generates data according to their individual settings.

Parameters:
Col - An array of Field objects collected by the MainGui
output - A String that contains the name of the file where the data will be saved.
Records - An integrity containing the total number of records the generator should create.
Parent - This is a reference to the configuration panel, so the user may return to it.
Method Detail

GenerateData

public void GenerateData()
The GenerateData Method Starts prepares the Fields and their respective generators, uses them to create the required data, and then cleans up the temporary space used. This method also updates the GUI with its progress so the end user can monitor the program.

run

public void run()
This method is used to run the generator in a separate thread from main.
